  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation:\n\n1. International Level:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group standards\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act (in the United States)\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Risk assessment procedures\n\n4. Criminal Consequences:\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Regulatory Oversight:\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Securities regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms:\n- Internal control systems\n- Independent audits\n- Employee training programs\n- Risk management protocols\n\n7. Jurisdictional Variations:\n- Different countries have unique implementation approaches\n- Varying enforcement levels\n- Specific regulatory requirements\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
